Wavelet Scale Correspondance

library(centWaveP)
for (i in seq(1, 50, 5)) {
  wav = centWaveP:::return.wavelet('mexh') %>% { centWaveP:::scale.wavelet(i, .)$y }
  plot(wav)
  cat(sum(wav > 0), i, "\n")
  }

eic = { dnorm(seq(-6, 6, by =0.1)) } %>% { ./max(.) }
plot(eic)

for (i in seq(1, 50, 5)) {
  wav = cwt(eic, i, 'mexh')
  print(plot(wav, main = i))
  cat(sum(wav > 0), i, "\n")
}

eic = { dnorm(seq(-6, 6, by =0.1)) + dnorm(seq(-6, 6, by =0.1), mean = 3) } %>% { ./max(.) }
plot(eic)

  wav = cwt(eic, i, 'nmexh')
  print(plot(wav, main = i))
  cat(sum(wav < 0), i, "\n")
}
